What are the two basic rules for designing a recursive functions:

A:  ensure that there are at least two recursive calls in the body,and that each call is different
B:ensure that there are at least two recursive calls in the body,and that each call is different
C:identify base case(s),and ensure that each recursive call makes progress towards a base case
D:identify the recursive breakdown of the problem,and for each recursive call implement a separate helper function

